criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Meet the diagnosis of UC

          -  Mayo ≤10

          -  Patients do not receive any medicine, or if they are receiving medicine, it should be
             aminosalicylates and/or prednisone (dose ≤15mg and have taken at least 1 month), and
             must kept the same dose as before throughout the trial;

          -  Patients should have not received antibiotic, biologicals within 3 months prior to
             entering the study;

          -  Signing a written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with cardiac, encephalic, hepatic, nephric, hematopoietic system, psychotic
             or any other serious diseases;

          -  Pregnancy or lactation;

          -  The psychiatric patients;

          -  Current or prior history of neurosurgery, head injury, cerebrovascular insult, or
             brain trauma involving loss of consciousness;

          -  Learning disability;

          -  Claustrophobia;

          -  Presence of metallic implants in the body;
